  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior / Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Descriptions</strong></p><ol><li><p>Provide and supervise IT support to staff and students.</p></li><li><p>Diagnose and troubleshoot hardware, software, and network issues for desktops, laptops, iPads, printers, and other peripherals.</p></li><li><p>Manage operating system deployment, virtual environment, software installation, and patching processes.</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot server / network connectivity issues, including wired and wireless networks.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate server and network enhancement projects, including procurement and vendor management.</p></li><li><p>Manage MDM for student iPad PLD platform.</p></li><li><p>Maintain and improve technical documentation, SOPs, and knowledge base articles.</p></li><li><p>Provide excellent customer service and maintain a positive attitude while assisting end-users with their IT-related needs.</p></li></ol><p><br /><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Strong proficiency in the administration of Vmware, Hyper-v, Windows AD, MS365, MS Exchange, MS Sharepoint and networking devices (switches, firewalls, wireless network).</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with TCP/IP, LAN/WAN technologies, VPN, VLAN, and network monitoring tools.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of network security principles, endpoint protection, and data security best practices.</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage projects, procurement processes and vendor coordination.</p></li><li><p>Good interpersonal skills and problem solving skills.</p></li><li><p>Past experience with Education / MOE schools preferred.</p></li><li><p>This is a 2-year contract (renewable)</p></li></ul>",
