    "description": "<p>Founded in 1823, Raffles Institution (RI) provides its students with an all-round education through its integrated six-year Raffles Programme, which leads to the GCE A-Level certification for boys aged 13 to 18 and girls aged 17 to 18. The Raffles Programme, together with the school’s diversity and inclusivity efforts in the school’s curricular and co-curricular programming, develops students into thinkers, leaders and pioneers, who understand the basis of connecting with the wider community, and actively seek to serve others. Students will come to a greater awareness of their talents and gifts and learn where and how to put these talents to their best use.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
